<br>
What is the exact message of the BSOD?  In particular, what executable does it list as causing the error (i.e., ntkernel, nv_disp4.dll, etc.)?<br>
<br>
This may not be a display driver issue at all.  The only driver revision which I know has problems with DAOC is 21.83.  The 23.11s (latest on Nvidia's official site) should work just fine.<br>
<br>
Some preliminary things you want to check:<ul><li>Do you have your latest motherboard drivers?</li><br>
<li>Did you install DirectX 8.1 from Microsoft?</li><br>
<li>Are your network/display/sound cards sharing an IRQ, through ACPI or otherwise?</li><br>
<li>Are your sound card drivers updated?</li><br>
<li>Are you using an SB Live! (in which case, do yourself a favor and toss it out the window)?</ul>More information about your setup (motherboard type, nature of error, types of PCI cards installed) would be helpful. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A> at: 1/31/02 9:25:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upakaraatzi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pakaraatzi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/1/02 3:23:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=269.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DAOC crashing with Nvidia card, tried most solutions.</span><hr size=1> I didn't read the <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroveboardpostingrulesandpolicy.showMessage?topicID=1.topic>rules</a> so I said a bunch of mean things that are not allowed. Please forgive my trollish outburst.<br>
